abstract: This excerpt describes an interactive art system that transforms body motion into audio and visual output. Sound is generated from the body positions/movements, and the user’s image is changed/visualized in response to those movements. The text mentions a user study/experience with kindergarten children, noting that when the children moved happily the system produced corresponding audio–visual changes.
